Description:
This is a beginner-friendly landing page created using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It consists of a navigation bar, a hero section with a call-to-action button, and basic interactivity using JavaScript.

Features:
✅ Responsive Navigation Bar
✅ Hero Section with Heading, Description, and Button
✅ JavaScript Alert on Button Click
✅ Simple and Clean Design

File Structure:
pgsql
Copy
Edit
my-landing-page
│
├── index.html   <-- HTML Structure
├── styles.css   <-- CSS Styles
├── script.js    <-- JavaScript Functionality
Technologies Used:
HTML5 → For page structure
CSS3 → For page styling
JavaScript (Vanilla JS) → For basic interactivity
How to Run the Project:
Download the project or clone the repository.
Open the index.html file in any web browser.
Click the "Click Me" button to see the JavaScript alert.
Code Explanation:
index.html: Contains the page content like the navbar, heading, button, etc.
styles.css: Adds visual styling like colors, padding, and responsiveness.
script.js: Adds a simple JavaScript function to trigger an alert on button click.
How the JavaScript Works:
It selects the button using getElementById()
Adds an event listener that listens for a button click.
When clicked, it triggers an alert() message.
Future Improvements:
✅ Add smooth scrolling.
✅ Include form submission functionality.
✅ Enhance the design with CSS animations.
✅ Make it a multi-page website.
